Door County, Wisconsin

2024 Summer Concert Season

Birch Creek Music Performance Center is thrilled to present the highly anticipated 2024 summer concert season, featuring captivating performances by advanced student musicians and world-class faculty performing artists who study and teach by day and perform at night in the historic Dutton Concert Barn. Secure your tickets now and immerse yourself in the world of music at the picturesque Birch Creek campus, just three miles east of Egg Harbor.

Summer Music Academy

Registration for the 2024 summer music academy is now open!

The Birch Creek Experience

An engaging, inside look at the students and faculty who make up Birch Creek Music Performance Center’s residential music academy in Door County, Wisconsin.

Birch Creek Program Book

Business owners and organizations are invited to partner with Birch Creek by advertising in our program book.

The digital program, which you can open and browse through, is a flip book which includes ads (with links to each advertiser’s website), donor recognition, Birch Creek history, concert schedules and features on programs and outreach. For 2024, Birch Creek advertisers also receive a print ad in the physical program book which is distributed to thousands of concertgoers throughout the summer and fall at Birch Creek. Contact us by phone at (920) 868-3763 or by email for any questions regarding ad space in next season’s program book.

We hope you enjoy the Birch Creek Digital Program Book. Try our links – advertisers, concerts and more!

About Birch Creek Music Performance Center

Birch Creek Music Performance Center is an elite summer music academy located in the heart of Door County Wisconsin. Students, entering grade seven through graduating grade 12, attend from up to 15 states and from other countries. Our faculty are professional musicians, many of whom teach and perform at some of the most prestigious music schools in the country. Together, our students and faculty present over 30 concerts in the historic Dutton Barn and over 30 outreach concerts during our academy season. We offer four, two-week sessions in Percussion, Steel Pan & World Music; Symphony and two sessions of Big Band Jazz.

Our Mission

To provide intensive, performance-based instruction to promising young musicians by immersing them in a professional, mentoring environment.

Invest in Musicians

At Birch Creek we strive to provide access to every eligible student. Over half of our academy students receive a partial scholarship, funded by inspired, generous donors. Of these scholarship students, over 80% have indicated that they are pursuing a career in music. By investing in the Birch Creek scholarship program, you are literally changing the lives of future, professional musicians. Many of our students move on to be professional performing musicians and teachers. All have a keen appreciation for live music and performance. Would you join us in supporting our students and the future of music in our world?
